    "head_commit": {
      "id": "d382e86b9305a7f4cdfabdd1ac704976eace2ca4",
      "message": "Expanding S3 APIs (#14831)\n\nExpanding the S3 API.\n\n- Support for listing versions.\n- Support for generating signed URIs on `S3_File.presigned_uri`.\n- Added `bucket`, `key` and `version_id` onto `S3_File`.\n- Added `versions` to `S3_File`, allowing access to specific versions.\n- Added lazy ref cache on `S3_File` for `headObject` response.\n- Added the ability to head and get objects for specific versions.\n- Added `of_seconds`, `of_minutes` and `of_hours` to `Duration`, allowing a simpler widget.\n- Refactor a lot of the code:\n- Move AWS exception handling to Java.\n- S3 Utils request making is now merged into the client wrapper.\n- New approach for `HideableValue` from `EnsoSecret` to Java, which avoids passing the factory around.",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T19:21:29Z",
      "author": {
        "name": "James Dunkerley"
      }
    }
